{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Quantenna |model=QBox610 (QSKU-610) |fcc_date=07/05/2011 |is_manuf=No |availability=reference design |type=access point |fcc_id=ZM9-QSKU-610 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=1.5 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Quantenna |cpu1_model=QT1018BH;QT1018BH, AA11C0C0, A00101, 1046; |cpu1_cspeed=400 MHz |fla1=8 MiB |fla1_brand=Macronix |ram1=64 MiB |ram1_brand=EtronTech |ram1_model=EM6AA160TSA-5G |ram1_num=2 |wi1_chip1_brand=Quantenna |wi1_chip1_model=QT1018BH;QT1018BH, AA11C0C0, A00101, 1046; |wi1_chip2_brand=Quantenna |wi1_chip2_model=QT2518B;QT2518B-ES, AA00D1A0, E00007, 1044; |wi1_802dot11_protocols=an |wi1_ant_conn=U.FL |wi1_txchains=4 |wi1_rxchains=4 |wi1_sstreams=4 |eth_cpu=true |eth_chip2_brand=IC+ |eth_chip2_model=IP1001;IP1001 LF, 1024C13, GE3N930.18; |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=1 |addl_chips=5GHz Power Amplifier IC;Richwave;RTC6671;428, 6671, A109;4; |802dot11_protocols=an }} "QHS610_R2_QSKU", "Quantenna Communications", and '''Plotech''' PCB text appears to be silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
[http://www.quantenna.com/qhs-610.html QHS610 Product Page] [http://www.quantenna.com/pdf/QHS610_ProductBrief.pdf Product Brief]
All four antennas are noted as being '''ETHERTRONICS''' 1001017's in the FCC test report.
==Possibly used PSUs== The power supply shown in the FCC external photos is a '''Sunny Computer Technology Co., Ltd.''' SYS1428-1812-W2.
